<paragraph id="903E8E36ED878CD9595C5DFC1FF1B703" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="603D050478785137724D823052393903" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
<bibRefCitation id="2795F98C69E9BD2CED1463380C1984A1" author="Fassati, M" journalOrPublisher="Casopis Cesckoslovenske Spolecnosti Entomologicke" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" pagination="312 - 321" refId="B11" refString="Fassati, M, 1957. Eine neue Art und drei Rassen von Mittelasiatischen Bembidien aus der Untergattung Peryphus Steph. Casopis Cesckoslovenske Spolecnosti Entomologicke 54: 312 - 321" title="Eine neue Art und drei Rassen von Mittelasiatischen Bembidien aus der Untergattung Peryphus Steph." volume="54" year="1957">Fassati (1957)</bibRefCitation>
describes 
<taxonomicName id="FAB5354D9767F55697236E6886662A16" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) fuscicrum subsp. thibeticum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="fuscicrum" subGenus="Peryphus" subSpecies="thibeticum">Bembidion (Peryphus) fuscicrum thibeticum</taxonomicName>
ssp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="4509B95609C3DAA4CABBAD88F16D6EA5" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) fuscicrum subsp. fumipenne" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="fuscicrum" subGenus="Peryphus" subSpecies="fumipenne">Bembidion (Peryphus) fuscicrum fumipenne</taxonomicName>
nat. nov.; they are distinguished from the nominotypical form only by the coloration of the elytra. 
<bibRefCitation id="DA0B6CC336E43E6DB1104EDECB7C9408" author="Lindroth, CH" journalOrPublisher="Opuscula Entomologica, Supplementum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" pagination="201 - 408" refId="B23" refString="Lindroth, CH, 1963. The ground-beetles (Carabidae, excl. Cicindelinae) of Canada and Alaska. Part 3. Opuscula Entomologica, Supplementum 24: 201 - 408" title="The ground-beetles (Carabidae, excl. Cicindelinae) of Canada and Alaska. Part 3." volume="24" year="1963">Lindroth (1963)</bibRefCitation>
synonymizes the following taxa with 
<taxonomicName id="07CD9B571F9FA15B836901EEE1900EF0" genus="B." lsidName="B. obscurellum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="obscurellum">
<emphasis id="67263A31EEC2233ABD52325D1F90FD63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. obscurellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1845: 
<taxonomicName id="9AE1EA62718DED9EB59E1E0782358EF1" genus="B." lsidName="B. fuscicrum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="fuscicrum">
<emphasis id="348B02E49FBC88FF888597BCC6722692" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. fuscicrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1855, 
<taxonomicName id="264DA3C5320300F1460EFDE9D0348193" genus="B." lsidName="B. fuscicrum subsp. turanicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="fuscicrum" subSpecies="turanicum">
<emphasis id="9E78D929ECEF4FED0B87177744201083" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. fuscicrum turanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Csiki, 1928, 
<taxonomicName id="B4415D28EA216ED897A2F26F792A1B96" genus="B." lsidName="B. fumipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="3C807DE877CCFE7EFAB2376AA26E67C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ED12F5C8A5C60C04508CB76D293EBBBC" genus="B." lsidName="B. thibeticum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="thibeticum">
<emphasis id="4EE992A45F2FADF91CB8D2B7245C778F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. thibeticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the last two taxa because they are only color varieties. Kryzhanovskij et al. (1995) listed 
<taxonomicName id="8613E617EBEF1DA61F8E34DA0935BA59" genus="B." lsidName="B. turanicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="turanicum">
<emphasis id="DE7DD29B03404F8DEF225949D27D848D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. turanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="40F61E99D160FC5C744FD0F235CE56D1" genus="B." lsidName="B. obscurellum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="obscurellum">
<emphasis id="15342D938830ACC51E6BE9E597CCF588" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. obscurellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and retained 
<taxonomicName id="0701DEEDC3C80C0DF4A00E39287CC7E5" genus="B." lsidName="B. fumipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="488FEFD0B69FE673A927D1908C2E46F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="02CBF966AE557A19305F2EB55312727A" genus="B." lsidName="B. thibeticum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="thibeticum">
<emphasis id="E518D46DA7F07F9FC1A6298DD3EA9A8F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. thibeticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as varieties only; moreover 
<normalizedToken id="8F263ABBF03B6AB6849D3D65152C8FBE" originalValue="Belousovâ€™s">Belousov's</normalizedToken>
note (Kryzhanovskij et al. 1995: 85, note no. 158) reports that the subspecific situation of this polymorphic species is provisional. Recently, some authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="42E44CB6039B25702896FA572013D3C7" author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B26" refString="Lorenz, W, 2005. Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World (2nd edn.). Tutzing, 530 pp." title="Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World (2 nd edn.). Tutzing, 530 pp." year="2005">Lorenz 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C2FCEBACCF46587FEE5AFC2C7C794D66" author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B29" refString="Marggi, W, Toledano, L, Neri, P, 2017. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294-342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Brill, Leiden" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294 - 342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2017">Marggi et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
) still list 
<taxonomicName id="D915FE417CDC42318DD1AA9F4C114A0C" genus="B." lsidName="B. turanicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="turanicum">
<emphasis id="EA1DE7887B9EDFDB18C5E7C3BCE6E4F6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. turanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4194089039E82A76EDCDAB94A6B746C9" genus="B." lsidName="B. fumipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="A04BCB3F8F661AE32908E0E89410A9CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="DFCDDF3606914D4131F5EB265306A9D3" genus="B." lsidName="B. thibeticum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="thibeticum">
<emphasis id="16FD40F822195E8BBE6343C0B79D9BC4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. thibeticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="7F55DB5DA41F385F6ABB2C2901186B4F" genus="B." lsidName="B. obscurellum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="obscurellum">
<emphasis id="072055C03FCA1165337890A5C06ECFF7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. obscurellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DCD6A5CE00EF529A6A7F8A6F4693F68F" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
In light of our studies we maintain that the synonymies proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="03A22414BE595F5666D85013B3A0EB38" author="Lindroth, CH" journalOrPublisher="Opuscula Entomologica, Supplementum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" pagination="201 - 408" refId="B23" refString="Lindroth, CH, 1963. The ground-beetles (Carabidae, excl. Cicindelinae) of Canada and Alaska. Part 3. Opuscula Entomologica, Supplementum 24: 201 - 408" title="The ground-beetles (Carabidae, excl. Cicindelinae) of Canada and Alaska. Part 3." volume="24" year="1963">Lindroth (1963)</bibRefCitation>
were correct; moreover, our colleague Liang Hongbin (IZCAS, Beijing) confirms our opinion based on the study of hundreds of specimens from Mongolia that clearly show the variability of the species (Liang Hongbin, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="97C6348AE848BF81E6EB04F0E03B317F" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
Regarding 
<taxonomicName id="624B27332CD4E827D1F6BC5CA0E01717" authorityName="Lutshnik" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) obscurellum subsp. insperatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="obscurellum" subGenus="Peryphus" subSpecies="insperatum">Bembidion (Peryphus) obscurellum insperatum</taxonomicName>
Lutshnik, 1938, since its discriminating characters are not exclusive but shared by other subspecies, we evaluated the synonymy expressed in 
<bibRefCitation id="36924A6C9F5EC1435EFDB8506BC0A82D" author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B29" refString="Marggi, W, Toledano, L, Neri, P, 2017. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294-342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Brill, Leiden" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294 - 342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2017">Marggi et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
and add to the distribution of the species the Russian Caucasus (ST), the region mentioned in the description, as already reported in Kryzhanovskij et al. (1995): Ciscaucasia, Western and Central Greater Caucasus. Current distribution: 
<emphasis id="A23A7A850FE2089E9AA65AFD7BEA5E5A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">E</emphasis>
: DE, NT, 
<emphasis id="94AA6FBEAC8060F8DB8B145138AA85F0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">ST</emphasis>
, SV; 
<emphasis id="9E181994827CDC21A4DBF84D71DDCA2C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">A</emphasis>
: AF, CH, ES, IN, KA, KI, KZ, MG, TM, TR, WS, XIZ; 
<emphasis id="D5F1DDD3A1F27BCC2907B9C8B161903B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">NAR</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
